		<dc:creator>Alex Nesbitt</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Privacy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[politics]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[PROTECTIP]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Ron Wyden]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/?p=1601</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://wyden.senate.gov/">Senator Ron Wyden</a> is one of the few politicians anywhere who seems to really understands the Internet and the implications of Government intrusions into our privacy.  He stands up to the Media industry and it's attack on the rights of innovators.<br /><br />

If you want to understand some to the big issues like the so called <a href="http://opinion.latimes.com/opinionla/2011/09/technology-entrepreneurs-blast-the-protect-ip-act.html">PROTECT IP act</a> and how the government has a secret interpretation of the Patriot Act that would upset people if we only knew what it was.<br /><br />

If you have 35 minutes watch this video interview with Senator Wyden.<br /><br />

<iframe width="480" height="274" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Py0dShncLp4?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><p><a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/2011/10/19/a-senator-who-gets-the-internet/">A Senator Who Gets The Internet</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews">Digital Podcast</a></p>
]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://wyden.senate.gov/">Senator Ron Wyden</a> is one of the few politicians anywhere who seems to really understands the Internet and the implications of Government intrusions into our privacy.  He stands up to the Media industry and it&#8217;s attack on the rights of innovators.</p>
<p>If you want to understand some to the big issues like the so called <a href="http://opinion.latimes.com/opinionla/2011/09/technology-entrepreneurs-blast-the-protect-ip-act.html">PROTECT IP act</a> and how the government has a secret interpretation of the Patriot Act that would upset people if we only knew what it was.</p>
<p>If you have 35 minutes watch this video interview with Senator Wyden.</p>
<p><iframe width="480" height="274" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Py0dShncLp4?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p><a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/2011/10/19/a-senator-who-gets-the-internet/">A Senator Who Gets The Internet</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews">Digital Podcast</a></p>


