		<title>Audiobooks for Android</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/DigitalPodcast/~3/8CbZsbQiz0E/</link>
		<comments>http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/2011/05/11/audiobooks-for-android/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 11 May 2011 18:06:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Alex Nesbitt</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Android]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Audio Books]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[audiobook]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/?p=1531</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<img src="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/300x156xaudiobook_app_for_android-300x156.jpg.pagespeed.ic.U35YUVxYQf1.jpg" alt="" title="audiobooks for android" width="300" height="156" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1532" />I wanted to listen to my audiobooks on my Android and fortunately Audible has an app for that.  <a href="http://www.qksrv.net/click-1703039-10273919?url=http://www.audible.com/wireless/android&#038;source_code=COMA0213WS031709">Audible</a>'s <a href="http://www.audiobooksforandroid.com/">Audiobooks for Android</a> app was a pleasant surprise. 

I downloaded the app from the Android marketplace and install it on my phone.  I then entered my login info.  It immediately connected me to the Audible store.  From there, I was able to browse my library and download the audio books I wanted to listen too. The file was available for playing while the download occurred which meant minimal waiting. <p><a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/2011/05/11/audiobooks-for-android/">Audiobooks for Android</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews">Digital Podcast</a></p>
]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/300x156xaudiobook_app_for_android-300x156.jpg.pagespeed.ic.U35YUVxYQf1.jpg" alt="" title="audiobooks for android" width="300" height="156" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1532" />I wanted to listen to my audiobooks on my Android and fortunately Audible has an app for that.  <a href="http://www.qksrv.net/click-1703039-10273919?url=http://www.audible.com/wireless/android&#038;source_code=COMA0213WS031709">Audible</a>&#8217;s <a href="http://www.audiobooksforandroid.com/">Audiobooks for Android</a> app was a pleasant surprise. </p>
<p>I downloaded the app from the Android marketplace and install it on my phone.  I then entered my login info.  It immediately connected me to the Audible store.  From there, I was able to browse my library and download the audio books I wanted to listen too. The file was available for playing while the download occurred which meant minimal waiting. </p>
<p>I was also able to buy new audio books to play on my Android phone right from the app.  I did experience a slight bug in my first attempt to purchase an audiobook, but reloading the page and trying again seemed to fix the issue.</p>
<p>The import process was smooth and the player worked quite well. </p>
<p>I found a good overview of more audiobook apps at: <a href="http://www.audiobooksforandroid.com/best-android-audio-book-apps/">Android Audiobook Apps.</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews/2011/05/11/audiobooks-for-android/">Audiobooks for Android</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.digitalpodcast.com/podcastnews">Digital Podcast</a></p>


